  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Inspired by Tuvan throat singing, where a single voice produces audible overtones. High sync with bright tilt lifts individual harmonics into prominence above the fundamental. The formant position (O-vowel) mimics the throat shape of khoomi technique. Each note is a prayer sung in frequencies, not words.",
